Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph related

related

Purpose:
  Expand from one chunk or entity Wiki Graph URI to related objects.

Use when:
  - You have a selected chunk and need nearby Reading Graph chunks.
  - You have a selected entity and need Knowledge Graph triples involving it.

Usage:
  wikigraph <chunk-uri> related [query] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <entity-uri> related [query] [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--role <any|subject|object|self>] [--evidence [n]] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]

Returns:
  - Related full `wikg://...` URIs with labels or summaries.

Notes:
  - `related` starts from a known URI; `search` starts from query text.
  - Optional `query` uses the current FTS index to filter and rank only the related objects that would otherwise be returned; run `<archive-uri>/index build` first if the index is missing or outdated.
  - `--role` only applies to entity URIs. Default is `any`.
  - Add `--evidence` or `--evidence <n>` to include source evidence previews where available.
  - Evidence previews include 2 nearby sentences before and after by default. Use `--context 0` for exact cited ranges.
  - Read `wikigraph help retrieval` before choosing `--limit`, `--all`, `--json`, or `--jsonl`.
  - Use `wikigraph next <cursor>` for any returned `nextCursor`.
  - Returned URIs can be inspected or verified with other object commands.
  - Read `wikigraph help uri` before constructing object URIs.

Next steps:
  - Use `get` to inspect a readable returned URI.
  - Use `evidence` to verify a returned URI.
  - Use `pack` when one related object becomes the answer anchor.

Examples:
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/chunk/123 related
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 related "baptism"
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 related
  wikigraph wikg:///books/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 related --role subject --evidence
